There is broad agreement in the scientific community that the photocatalytic reaction rate for the different reaction schemes is adversely affected by a radiative or non-radiative recombination of photoexcited charge carriers18–22. However, it is very often not clear, if a fast electron-hole recombination or a slow charge diffusion to the reactive surface is the limiting factor for the reaction rate. Most known forms of TiO2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
