The mechanism of bacterial inactivation by photocatalysts is mostly described by an inital attack of the cell membrane by photogenerated hydroxyl radicals leading to lipid peroxidation29,33. Subsequent oxidative attacks to intracellular components cause the final cell death. Wolfrum et al. could even prove a complete mineralization of E. coli bacteria to CO2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
