IMPS and IMVS are powerful techniques to extract photoelectrochemical kinetic constants for majority and minority charge carriers in semiconductors by applying a small sinusoidal perturbation to the incident light intensity18,21,22,24,26,39. In IMPS the photocurrent-time response is measured under closed-circuit conditions at a defined DC bias potential. At a bias potential more positive than the OCP the photogenerated majority carrier electrons diffuse to the current collecting back-contact of the TiO2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
